<h2>Real Examples of Trends That Detection Caught Early</h2>
<p>Trend detection sounds abstract. Here are concrete cases where detection systems caught a trend 4 to 12 weeks before peak.</p>
<p><strong>Generative AI tools (2022 to 2023).</strong> ChatGPT launched in November 2022. Trend detection systems flagged the topic by mid-December. Publishers who wrote AI tool guides in January 2023 captured massive traffic through Q2. Late entrants in May 2023 fought for scraps.</p>
<p><strong>Vibe coding (2024).</strong> A niche term for prompt-driven software development. Surfaced on niche Twitter and Hacker News in spring 2024. Search demand followed by July. Publishers who captured the term early dominated SERP.</p>
